<plot>Profiling the small town of Willcox, Arizona, during the biggest day of the year, its annual celebration honoring hometown hero Rex Allen, last of the silver screen cowboys, this film explores the economic and educational challenges of rural living. With limitations on local employment opportunities and paths for higher education, students graduating from high school often leave town to seek their fortunes elsewhere.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?320766</url></doc>
